Red meat, dairy products and chocolate can help to facilitate VZK.
Red meat and chocolate is customary to assume as nightmare for your digestive tract.
But recent studies speak about the reverse: the diet, rich in meat proteins and by dairy products, it can help to facilitate symptoms in those, who suffer the inflammatory diseases of bowels.
This incurable illness, from which suffer approximately 1.3 million people in the USA and 300000 in Great Britain, leads to colic and inflation of stomach, chronic or bloody diarrhea, decrease in weight and extreme fatigue.
Usually for the softening of symptoms by patient they advise to avoid meat and dairy products, but researchers from the Washington university established that the main amino acid of protein tryptophan contributes to the production of the immune cells, which increase the tolerance of bowels.
The chief researcher doctor Marco Kolonna explained that the immune cells in the bowels follow the fact so that the malicious microbes, which enter with the food, would not penetrate in the body.
The cells, capable of starting inflammatory process, are balanced by the cells, which increase tolerance, protecting body and in this case without damaging on sensitive cloths.
If equilibrium too strongly is disrupted to the side of inflammation, this can lead to the inflammatory diseases of bowels.
Experiments showed that in the mice, that have the specific bacterium in the bowels, cells the increasing tolerance appear.
But to this bacterium is necessary tryptophan - one of the construction elements of protein, in order to start the appearance of these cells.
Professor column said: “We established the connection between one type of bacteria - Lactobacillus reuteri, which is the part of normal mikrobioma of bowels, and by the development of the population of the cells, which increase tolerance.
The more tryptophan contained in the nourishment of mice, the greater these immune cells they had”.
It assumed that the same will work in the people: the combination L. to reuteri and rich in tryptophan diet can contribute more tolerant and less inclined to the inflammations medium in the bowels.
Postdok doctor Louise Cervantes-Barraganvas, studying the variety increasing immune cells of the increasing tolerance, revealed that in one group of experimental mice these cells were, and in another group, which belonged to the same line, but it was contained separately, it was not them.
It assumed that the difference can be caused by mikrobiomami of bowels of mice - associations of bacteria, viruses and caps, which usually live in the gastrointestinal tract.
DNA of the cells of bowels of mice they were sekvenirovany, and were discovered six types of bacteria, which are present in the mice, that have immune cells, but absentees in the mice, that do not have them.
The mice, grown in the sterile medium, that did not have good mikrobioma and that did not develop this type of immune cells, obtained L. reuteri, and immune cells in them appeared.
In order to understand, as bacteria they influence immune system, researchers grew L. reuteri in the liquid medium and they then transferred the small portions of liquid;without the bacteria, to the underdeveloped immune cells, isolated from the mice.
Immune cells became the cells, which increase tolerance.
When active component was isolated from the liquid, this proved to be the by-product of processing tryptophan, known as indole-3-milk acid.
When researchers doubled a quantity of tryptophan in the food of mice, a quantity of these cells increased approximately by 50 percent, but when the level of tryptophan was lowered doubly, a quantity of cells also fell two times.
Doctor Cervantes-Barragan explains, that the people have the same increasing tolerance cells as in mice, and majority of us has L. reuteri in its gastrointestinal circuit.
It is unknown, do contribute the by-products of tryptophan from L. to reuteri to the development of cells in people so, as in mice, but in people, which suffer the inflammatory diseases of bowels, were discovered defects in the genes, connected with tryptophan.
She speaks: “Possibly, the development of these cells to us must be strengthened, since on these cells it depends inflammatory processes on the internal surface of the guts.
The high levels of tryptophan in the presence L. reuteri potentially can lead to the expansion of their population”.
