Those lasting not one decade of the effort of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of republic Buryatia (East Siberia) on the establishment of just tariffs for the users of electrical energy begin to give fruits.
Since September 1 the cost of electric power in the low voltage for the industrial recipients is reduced to 25%.
The federal antitrust service of the country in accordance with the decision of government RF “about the introduction of changes in the rules of the wholesale market for electrical energy and power and into the summary forecast balance of production and deliveries to the electrical energy (power) within the framework of the unified power system of Russia according to the subjects of the Russian Federation” (from 17.07.2017 g. of № 842) established indicative prices of electric power and power for the industrial users of republic Buryatia.
As a result the cost of electrical energy for the buryat commodity producers decreases by fourth, which will considerably facilitate life to small and average enterprises and to individual owners.
Many decades the leaders of republic covered the thresholds of Moscow offices in the vain attempts to make even region in the tariffs with the adjacent Irkutsk region with the cascade of hydroelectric power plants in Angar, which escapes from Baykal, main water-collecting territory for which is Buryatia.
And motions only in this year began.
In March tariffs on the electrical energy for populating the republic are reduced from 4.24 rub of /kVtch to 3.93 rub of /kVtch, or by 7.3%.
With the start of Buryatia on the resolution of Federal Government in the enumeration of the territories of the price zones of wholesale market, for which are established the special features of the functioning of wholesale and retail markets came the turn of industrial users.
In the opinion of the analysts, the only beginning, since the population of Irkutsk region pays for the kilowatt/the hour of 1.01 rubles.
But no one dares to name the approximate date of new tariff motions to the side of reduction for Buryatia at least.
